description.p:
A first aspect of the invention provides a network access method, including:
transmitting, by a base station, data transmission configuration information to a terminal, where the data transmission configuration information comprises start time, an effective duration of data transmission, and randomization granularity, wherein a time span is calculated by the terminal according to the start time and the effective duration of the data transmission;
receiving, by the base station, a random access request, where the random access request is sent by the terminal when a service triggering time arrives, the service triggering time is a start time of a time interval randomly selected by the terminal from at least one time interval, and the at least one time interval is obtained by the terminal by dividing the time span according to the randomization granularity.

A second aspect of the invention provides a base station, including:
transmitting unit, configured to transmit data transmission configuration information to a terminal, where the data transmission configuration information comprises start time, an effective duration of data transmission, and randomization granularity, and a time span is calculated by the terminal according to the start time and the effective duration of the data transmission;
receiving unit, configured to receive a random access request, where the random access request is sent by the terminal when a service triggering time arrives, the service triggering time is a start time of a time interval randomly selected by the terminal from at least one time interval, and the at least one time interval is obtained by the terminal by dividing the time span according to the randomization granularity.

A third aspect of the invention provides a network access system, including: a base station according mentioned above and a terminal, wherein the terminal includes:
an obtaining unit, configured to obtain data transmission configuration information transmitted by the base station, where the data transmission configuration information comprises start time, an effective duration of data transmission, and randomization granularity;
a determining unit, configured to determine service triggering time according to a predetermined triggering time randomization policy; and
an access unit, configured to initiate a random access request procedure at the determined service triggering time;
where the determining unit comprises:
a calculating module, configured to calculate a time span of the data transmission according to the start time and the effective duration of the data transmission;
a dividing module, configured to divide the time span into at least one time interval according to the randomization granularity; and
a selecting module, configured to randomly select a time interval from the at least one time interval, wherein start time of the selected time interval is the service triggering time.

